name: Air Fryer Zesty Cheddar Biscuits
author: thedailygourmet
summary: I love the Cheddar biscuits a popular seafood restaurant has, but also love blending ingredients to create a fusion.
ingredients: ¾ cup freshly shredded sharp Cheddar cheese
2 tablespoons canned chopped green chile peppers
directions: Preheat an air fryer to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C) for 5 minutes
Combine flour, Cheddar cheese, milk, green chile peppers,  , garlic powder, cumin, and sugar in a medium bowl
Blend together until a dough forms
Line the air fryer basket with a parchment paper round
Drop dough into the basket using a spring-hinged scoop
Meanwhile, mix melted butter and taco seasoning mix together for the topping
Separate biscuits and brush with taco-seasoned butter
